examples.en: I could not comprehend her refusal to help.
I did not fully comprehend what had happened.
They did not comprehend how hard he had struggled.
It took me a while to comprehend algebra.
Do you comprehend the meaning of this letter?
He failed to comprehend the seriousness of the problem.
She cannot comprehend the extent of the disaster.
Finally, she comprehended that he wanted his pay.
Egypt comprehended anciently a prodigious number of cities.
It may be hard to comprehend how much this gift means for my country.
